  "assistantText": "Your button counter circuit is ready! 🎉 Here's a full breakdown:\n\n---\n\n## 🔌 Wiring Table\n\n| Arduino Pin | Component | Function |\n|-------------|-----------|----------|\n| **D2** | 7-Seg segment **a** (via 220Ω) | Top segment |\n| **D3** | 7-Seg segment **b** (via 220Ω) | Top-right segment |\n| **D4** | 7-Seg segment **c** (via 220Ω) | Bottom-right segment |\n| **D5** | 7-Seg segment **d** (via 220Ω) | Bottom segment |\n| **D6** | 7-Seg segment **e** (via 220Ω) | Bottom-left segment |\n| **D7** | 7-Seg segment **f** (via 220Ω) | Top-left segment |\n| **D8** | 7-Seg segment **g** (via 220Ω) | Middle segment |\n| **GND** | 7-Seg **common cathode** | Display ground |\n| **D9** | Button pin **a** | Button input (INPUT_PULLUP) |\n| **GND** | Button pin **b** | Button ground |\n\nEach segment has its own **220Ω series resistor** to limit current safely.\n\n---\n\n## 📟 How It Works\n\n| Action | Result |\n|--------|--------|\n| Press button | Count increments by 1 |\n| Count reaches 9 → press again | Wraps back to **0** |\n| Startup | Always shows **0** |\n\n- Uses **INPUT_PULLUP** on D9 — button connects pin to GND when pressed (active LOW)\n- **Falling-edge detection** prevents multiple counts per press\n- **50ms debounce delay** avoids false triggers from mechanical bounce\n\n---\n\n## ⚡ Power Budget\n\n| Item | Current Draw |\n|------|-------------|\n| Each lit segment | ~(5V − 2V) / 220Ω ≈ **13.6mA** |\n| Max segments lit (digit 8) | 7 × 13.6mA ≈ **95mA** (shared across 7 pins) |\n| Per Arduino pin (1 segment) | **~13.6mA** ✅ (well under 20mA limit) |\n| Button pin | ~0mA (INPUT_PULLUP, no current at rest) |\n| **Total draw** | **≤ 95mA** ✅ (Uno supports ~200mA total I/O) |\n\nAll pins are safely within the 20mA per-pin limit and the board's total budget. ✅",
